  "text": "The error 'ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable' is not defined in the etcd-io/etcd repository itself; it is part of the go.etcd.io/raft/v3 library. However, the snapshot availability check during Raft log catch-up is implemented across multiple files in etcd-io/etcd:\n\n1. **server/etcdserver/server.go** contains the core logic:\n   - `snapshotIfNeededAndCompactRaftLog()` (line ~2700) implements the snapshot catch-up check by maintaining SnapshotCatchUpEntries worth of log entries. If a follower falls behind more than this threshold, a snapshot is needed.\n   - `applyAll()` orchestrates the apply flow, calling `snapshotIfNeededAndCompactRaftLog()` after applying entries.\n   - `applySnapshot()` handles applying received snapshots to the node state.\n\n2. **server/etcdserver/snapshot_merge.go**:\n   - `createMergedSnapshotMessage()` (line 31) creates snapshot messages combining v2 store metadata and v3 KV snapshots for sending to followers during catch-up.\n\n3. **server/etcdserver/api/snap/snapshotter.go**:\n   - `LoadNewestAvailable()` (line 113) loads the newest available snapshot that matches WAL snapshots, with error handling for `ErrNoSnapshot`.\n   - `loadMatching()` (line 126) implements the actual snapshot availability check logic.\n\n4. **server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/snapshot_sender.go**:\n   - `send()` (line 67) sends snapshots to remote peers and handles snapshot failures by reporting `raft.SnapshotFailure` to trigger retry logic.\n\nThe catch-up flow: When a node rejoins, if its log index has fallen too far behind (> SnapshotCatchUpEntries entries), etcd triggers snapshot creation via `createMergedSnapshotMessage()` and sends it via `snapshot_sender.send()`. If the snapshot is unavailable (temporary I/O issues, ongoing snapshots), the error would be caught and the follower would retry after backoff, implementing the temporary unavailability handling."
}

